## Compile and run the application
1. Navigate to the project directory and check/define your API root URL   
in the environment file (src/environments/environment.development.ts)

2. Install dependencies based on package.json:   
```npm install```   
if necessary, you can also update dependencies to their latest versions by running:   
```npm update```   

3. Disable Angular CLI analytics (optional):   
```ng analytics disable```

4. Start the development server:   
```npm start```   
'npm start' is an alias for 'ng serve' so a local development server will be started and the application will be compiled.  
The application will be available at http://localhost:4200/ in your web browser.
